This paper proposes a novel approach for multi-step-ahead time series prediction using support vector regression (SVR) and compares the performance of different prediction strategies. The paper focuses on machine learning techniques and algorithms for time series prediction, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of SVR and MIMO strategy indicates that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the computational cost of different prediction strategies, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of datasets and the assessment of prediction accuracy, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
